[1]

Date: Fri, 14 Mar 2003
From: Shamsudeen Fagbo <oshamsudeen@hotmail.com>
Source: Arab News, 12 Mar 2003 [edited]
<http://arabnews.com/Article.asp?ID=23604>

Poultry Imports from EU Banned Over Bird Flu
--------------------------------------------
Saudi Arabia has slapped a temporary ban on the import of chicken products
from the European Union after the discovery of suspected cases of bird flu
in Europe, a newspaper reported yesterday.

The Al-Watan daily said the Commerce Ministry has sent its decision to the
Council of Saudi Chambers of Commerce and Industry and quality control
laboratories instructing them to prevent the entry of any European chicken
products.

Saudi Arabia imports some 120 000 tons of chicken products annually from
the EU valued at 133 million USD.

Bird flu, also known as avian influenza, is a viral disease that is highly
contagious to chickens, turkeys, ducks, and other birds but not dangerous
for humans.

